05/05/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- During talks in Tashkent on Friday (2 May), Foreign Minister Mladen Ivanic and EBRD President Jean Lemierre discussed future EBRD assistance to BiH. 
The EBRD held its annual meeting in Uzbekistan's capital at the end of last week. 
Ivanic and Lemierre agreed that the focus should be on improving the investment climate in the country. 
New investment initiatives will be drafted over the next few months and discussed by the EBRD board of directors in September. 
(PBS BiH - 03/05/03)
